Torin::

"He said as many as possible." Torin says, digging into another 
crate.  "I figure once we've covered this place we should have enough 
to at least get a start on whatever he's got in mind."  It's rather 
comical listening to his voice come from the inside of a packing 
crate with the back half of a big lizard sticking out of it.

--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Jeff" <x_rauq_x@y...> wrote:
> -- Noir --
> 
> Noir scrounges around in the storage box a bit more and finds 
> another communicator beacon. After dragging it out from under a 
> rusted blaster, and small computer frame, she tosses it into the 
> box. 
> 
> "Any idea how many of these things Devilcat wanted us to find?" 
Noir 
> asks Torin as she straightens, and looks over at the lizard-bot.
